05/03/2010
BERLIN, Germany -- A court in Dusseldorf on Thursday (March 4th) convicted a Turkish citizen and a German citizen of Turkish origin, along with two other Germans, for involvement in a plot aimed at creating what a judge described as "a second September 11th". Turkish national Adem Yilmaz was sentenced to 11 years in prison, while Attila Selek, a Turk who holds a German passport, received five years. The two Germans, identified as Fritz Gelowicz and Daniel Schneider, received 12 years each. The four allegedly planned to target US military facilities in Germany along with civilian sites in 2007. (BBC, Hurriyet, CNN Turk, VoA - 04/03/10)
